Subject: Liminal Draw Layer

Description: Between-focus layer where periphery relates to focus by correlation or causation.

& [LiminalDrawLayer] is the between-focus layer that explains attention movement
  + [layer_key] is liminal_draw
  + [node_role] is N:liminal:<relation_key>
  + [edge_role] is E:draws_attention:<relation_key>
  + [traversal_policy] is F:\.sop\platform\AttentionTraversalPolicy.sop when periphery must fold and unwind before focus
  + [correlation_draw] is periphery becomes relevant through shared features or repeated touch
  + [causal_draw] is periphery becomes relevant because it changes, blocks, enables, or explains focus
  + [stage_draw] is relation appears between operation steps, stages, or internal reflection moments

  = must: name whether draw is correlation, causation, or both
  = must: use traversal_policy when draw requires cross-reference, fold, unwind, or triangulated probe
  = must: preserve uncertainty when causation is only hypothesized
  = should: promote pressure and impact draw candidates into focus review
  - never: call correlation causation without support
